Hey, don't get mad at Bradley.  Not even the referee.  Get mad at the judges who score the fight, especially the 2 motherf**kers that gave the decision for Bradley.

It's about time the sport of boxing move forward into the 21st century and use a scoreboard scoring system so everybody can see the round by round scoring for each fighter as the fight moves along.  I'm pretty sure the Pacquiao team would have reacted very strongly if they can see on the scoreboard how the judges were scoring the fight, especially for the last 4 rounds of the fight.  Had a system like this been in effect for this fight -- it would not have ended in a decision but a very definite KO or referee stops contest.  NO judges decion needed.
